WEBVTT

00:00.467 --> 00:04.570
You will not
believe what happened
at laser tag last night.

00:04.572 --> 00:07.306
People
freaked out because
a creepy man in a suit

00:07.308 --> 00:09.141
wouldn't leave
their kids alone?

00:09.143 --> 00:10.442
No.

00:10.444 --> 00:12.344
Well, yeah,
pretty much.

00:12.346 --> 00:14.346
(LASER GUNS FIRING)

00:15.582 --> 00:17.282
(BARNEY LAUGHS TRIUMPHANTLY)

00:17.284 --> 00:18.450
Come on!

00:18.452 --> 00:20.386
(EXCLAIMING)

00:20.388 --> 00:22.721
BOY: Ow! My shoulder!

00:22.723 --> 00:24.123
Come on.

00:24.125 --> 00:24.823
(EXCLAIMS IN FRUSTRATION)

00:24.825 --> 00:28.160
Stinson, my office!
Now!

00:28.162 --> 00:29.661
Crap.

00:30.196 --> 00:31.563
Disorderly game play,

00:31.565 --> 00:34.466
three counts of shoving,
and now this!

00:34.468 --> 00:36.335
Stinson, you're a liability!

00:36.337 --> 00:39.905
I know I don't play by
your "precious rules,"
McCracken,

00:39.907 --> 00:42.274
but damn it,
I get results!

00:42.276 --> 00:42.875
(BANGS TABLE)

00:42.877 --> 00:45.577
Look,
you're a good
laser tag player,

00:45.579 --> 00:47.413
maybe the best
I've ever seen.

00:47.415 --> 00:50.649
But one of these days,
you're gonna get someone hurt.

00:50.651 --> 00:52.418
Maybe even yourself.

00:52.420 --> 00:54.286
You just forget what
it's like out there.

00:54.288 --> 00:57.322
You've had your
fat ass stuck behind
that desk for too long.

00:57.324 --> 00:59.425
That's it!
You're out of
here, Stinson!

00:59.427 --> 01:01.393
Hand in your gun
and your ID badge!

01:01.395 --> 01:03.662
With pleasure.

01:06.433 --> 01:09.802
Please don't do this.
This game is all I got.

01:09.804 --> 01:15.107
And I've
almost got enough tickets for
the remote-control helicopter.

01:15.109 --> 01:16.542
Please.

01:18.178 --> 01:20.913
I can't believe
I'm doing this.

01:20.915 --> 01:22.915
But
I'm gonna give
you one last shot.

01:22.917 --> 01:24.016
(SIGHING)

01:24.018 --> 01:27.886
But so help me,
if you so much as
step one toe out of line,

01:27.888 --> 01:30.189
you're gonna
be playing<i> Duck Hunt</i>
in your mama's basement

01:30.191 --> 01:32.357
so fast it's gonna
make your head spin.

01:32.359 --> 01:34.693
Now, get out of here!

01:37.864 --> 01:40.432
You won't regret this.

01:41.134 --> 01:42.668
(LAUGHS EVILLY)

01:42.670 --> 01:44.303
(LASER GUN FIRING)

01:44.871 --> 01:46.338
Whoa.

01:46.340 --> 01:51.210
That's it, Stinson.
You're banned for life!

01:51.212 --> 01:53.679
<i>(POIGNANT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

01:53.681 --> 01:57.516
No!

01:57.518 --> 01:58.851
(SOBBING)

02:10.797 --> 02:14.433
I can't believe you got
kicked out of laser tag.
What are you gonna do?

02:14.435 --> 02:17.369
What am I gonna do?
What am I gonna do?

02:17.371 --> 02:19.938
I'll tell you what
Ted and I are gonna do.

02:19.940 --> 02:24.710
We're gonna break in
after hours and TP
the place.

02:24.712 --> 02:28.580
Barney,
we are too old to cover
a place in toilet paper

02:28.582 --> 02:30.582
just because they won't
let you play laser tag.

02:30.584 --> 02:33.318
And for that matter,
we're too old for
laser tag.

02:33.320 --> 02:36.421
Ted, laser tag knows
no age restrictions.

02:36.423 --> 02:38.390
Kind of like
stripping in
the Midwest.

02:38.392 --> 02:39.958
Yeah, whatever.

02:39.960 --> 02:42.427
I'm adding laser tag
to the Murtaugh list.

02:42.429 --> 02:44.530
Oh, jeez, not
the Murtaugh list.

02:44.532 --> 02:45.364
Yeah.
What's the Murtaugh list?

02:45.366 --> 02:47.466
<i>OLDER TED: The Murtaugh list</i>
<i>is something that came into</i>
<i>being</i>

02:47.468 --> 02:48.967
<i>around the time I turned 30.</i>

02:48.969 --> 02:52.304
<i>It all started with your</i>
<i>uncle Marshall's beer bong.</i>

02:52.306 --> 02:53.572
(CHEERING)

02:53.574 --> 02:57.342
<i>When</i>
<i>we were in our early 20s,</i>
<i>every time we had a party,</i>

02:57.344 --> 02:58.010
<i>that beer bong came out.</i>

02:58.012 --> 03:00.846
<i>And around the time we</i>
<i>turned 30, same thing.</i>

03:00.848 --> 03:04.516
<i>Of course, in our early 20s,</i>
<i>the next day would go like</i>
<i>this.</i>

03:04.518 --> 03:05.584
(EXCLAIMING EXCITEDLY)

03:05.586 --> 03:10.389
<i>But by the time we were 30,</i>
<i>the next day would go like</i>
<i>this.</i>

03:10.391 --> 03:11.089
(MOANING)

03:11.091 --> 03:15.160
<i>Then one day,</i>
<i>in the throes of the</i>
<i>worst hangover of my life,</i>

03:15.162 --> 03:16.962
<i>I realized there</i>
<i>was only one person</i>

03:16.964 --> 03:19.097
<i>in the world that</i>
<i>I could relate to.</i>

03:19.099 --> 03:20.265
<i>Detective</i>
<i>Roger Murtaugh,</i>

03:20.267 --> 03:24.536
<i>played by Danny Glover in</i>
<i>the '80s noir masterpiece</i>
<i>Lethal Weapon,</i>

03:24.538 --> 03:27.039
<i>known for his</i>
<i>oft-quoted catchphrase...</i>

03:27.041 --> 03:28.307
I'm too old for this...

03:28.309 --> 03:32.110
<i>OLDER TED: Stuff. He said,</i>
<i>"I'm too old for this stuff."</i>

03:32.112 --> 03:33.745
It's sad to admit,
but as you get older,

03:33.747 --> 03:35.847
there's
just certain things
you can't do anymore.

03:35.849 --> 03:38.884
That's why I have this list,
so I never
make the mistake of thinking

03:38.886 --> 03:40.953
that I can still
pull an all-nighter.

03:40.955 --> 03:44.690
Oh.
I'm too old
for that stuff.

03:44.692 --> 03:47.259
Or eat an entire
pizza in one sitting.

03:47.261 --> 03:49.995
I'm too old
for that stuff.

03:49.997 --> 03:53.298
Or hang posters on
your wall without
frames.

03:53.300 --> 03:56.301
Riggs. Riggs!

03:56.303 --> 03:58.403
I'm too old
for that stuff.

03:58.405 --> 04:01.073
By the way,
how good is
<i>Lethal Weapon?</i>

04:01.075 --> 04:02.841
I don't know.
It's kind of
a rip-off.

04:02.843 --> 04:05.844
Old guy paired up with
a young, renegade cop.

04:05.846 --> 04:07.813
Sound familiar?

04:08.014 --> 04:10.415
<i>Mackleroy and LeFleur.</i>

04:10.417 --> 04:13.952
Don't tell me you
guys have never seen
<i>Mackleroy and LeFleur.</i>

04:13.954 --> 04:17.389
It's the
greatest Canadian
action movie of all time.

04:17.391 --> 04:21.727
Mackleroy is
a young, renegade Mountie
whose horse was just killed

04:21.729 --> 04:22.794
by evil Americans...
Wait.

04:22.796 --> 04:25.831
...while LeFleur, his grouchy,
old, African-Canadian partner,

04:25.833 --> 04:27.065
just bought a cozy
ice-fishing shack...

04:27.067 --> 04:29.368
Wait.
...in northern Alberta.

04:29.370 --> 04:31.236
Now...
Stop it!

04:31.238 --> 04:32.738
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

04:32.740 --> 04:33.505
I got to go.

04:33.507 --> 04:35.374
Bye, baby.
Have fun at practice.

04:35.376 --> 04:38.477
Practice?
Is he doing that
one-man band thing again?

04:38.479 --> 04:40.379
'Cause that was a bummer.

04:40.381 --> 04:43.482
<i>OLDER TED:</i>
<i>Actually, Marshall had</i>
<i>just taken over as coach</i>

04:43.484 --> 04:45.350
<i>for Lily's</i>
<i>kindergarten</i>
<i>basketball team.</i>

04:45.352 --> 04:49.187
<i>He thought it'd be fun,</i>
<i>but Lily saw it as</i>
<i>something more.</i>

04:49.189 --> 04:50.355
<i>Dad practice.</i>

04:50.357 --> 04:51.456
Hi.

04:51.458 --> 04:53.091
Hey! Oh, my gosh!

04:53.093 --> 04:55.294
Orange slices.
That is so sweet.

04:55.296 --> 04:56.295
What are you doing here?

04:56.297 --> 05:00.565
I couldn't resist. I wanted to
see Coach Marshmallow do his
thing.

05:00.567 --> 05:02.167
(LAUGHING) Oh! Okay.

05:02.169 --> 05:04.936
Hey, kids,
who wants to
knock off early

05:04.938 --> 05:07.873
and have
some of these
here orange slices?

05:07.875 --> 05:09.341
(CHEERING)

05:09.343 --> 05:13.011
Yeah? Well, you can't!
Because oranges are
for winners,

05:13.013 --> 05:16.715
and you little turds haven't
even made a single shot yet!

05:16.717 --> 05:18.216
You're embarrassing
yourselves,

05:18.218 --> 05:19.818
you're embarrassing
Miss Aldrin,

05:19.820 --> 05:23.155
and worst of all,
you're embarrassing me!

05:23.157 --> 05:26.258
That's it!
Suicides! Baseline! Now!

05:26.260 --> 05:27.859
(BLOWS WHISTLE)

05:27.861 --> 05:29.027
Run.

05:30.430 --> 05:35.300
Ted, there is not
a single thing on here
that you are too old to do.

05:35.302 --> 05:38.036
In fact, if
you did everything
on the Murtaugh list,

05:38.038 --> 05:39.905
I'd call that
a pretty fun
weekend.

05:39.907 --> 05:41.640
Barney,
you are not
18 anymore.

05:41.642 --> 05:45.577
If you did
everything on that
list, you would die.

05:45.945 --> 05:48.113
That wasn't a challenge.
Challenge accepted.

05:48.115 --> 05:53.051
In the next 24 hours,
I'm going to do every
single thing on this list.

05:53.053 --> 05:58.323
And after I do, you will TP
the laser tag place with me.

05:58.325 --> 05:59.458
And if you can't do it?

05:59.460 --> 06:03.829
I will spend three hours
listening to you
talk about architecture.

06:03.831 --> 06:05.764
You have got
yourself a deal.

06:05.766 --> 06:07.966
Robin,
will you do the honors?

06:08.434 --> 06:09.835
A gentlemen's agreement!

06:09.837 --> 06:11.002
Huzzah!
Huzzah!

06:11.004 --> 06:12.938
All right, chumps,
let's do this.

06:12.940 --> 06:16.641
Barney Stinson!

06:16.643 --> 06:19.411
You really want to make this
bet with him? You know how
he is.

06:19.413 --> 06:22.114
Robin, there is
some pretty tough
stuff on that list.

06:22.116 --> 06:26.451
(LAUGHING) Do
you really think Barney's
gonna get his ear pierced?

06:26.453 --> 06:28.520
"Get ear pierced." Check.

06:28.522 --> 06:32.457
All right, I'm off to go
do laundry at Mom's house.

06:37.296 --> 06:40.332
Hey, you guys mind if
I crash on your futon
tonight?

06:40.334 --> 06:41.633
We don't have a futon.

06:41.635 --> 06:43.402
Put it over there, boys.

06:43.404 --> 06:44.703
What's going on?
It's on the Murtaugh list.

06:44.705 --> 06:48.974
"Crash on a friend's futon
instead of getting a hotel
room."

06:48.976 --> 06:51.576
I am too old
for that stuff.

06:51.578 --> 06:53.044
Dude,
what's going
on with your ear?

06:53.046 --> 06:56.848
It looks like the inside of
a jack-o'-lantern on
November 3rd.

06:56.850 --> 06:59.284
What, this?
Just a little infectsh.

06:59.286 --> 07:01.653
Nothing a young guy
like me can't shake
off.

07:01.655 --> 07:04.289
Plus, "Put off going to
the doctor," on the list.

07:04.291 --> 07:05.457
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

07:05.459 --> 07:07.359
Oh. Hold on.

07:08.594 --> 07:09.594
Go for...

07:09.596 --> 07:11.029
(YELLS IN PAIN)

07:11.031 --> 07:13.131
(CACKLING)

07:13.232 --> 07:13.932
Keep running!

07:13.934 --> 07:18.270
You know what's funny is
I was supposed to come
here to teach them...

07:18.272 --> 07:20.505
Do not stop running!

07:20.507 --> 07:26.611
This whole time,
they've been the ones
who are teaching me. Hey!

07:26.613 --> 07:27.412
(KID SCREAMING)

07:27.414 --> 07:31.383
That's
not running!
That's falling!

07:31.385 --> 07:37.389
<i>OLDER TED: The next morning,</i>
<i>Barney woke up on the futon</i>
<i>in our living room.</i>

07:37.391 --> 07:39.124
(SCREAMING IN PAIN)

07:41.494 --> 07:43.562
Check.

07:43.564 --> 07:47.666
"Drinking shots
with strangers."
Check.

07:47.668 --> 07:50.368
You okay, Barney?
It looks like you
hurt your back.

07:50.370 --> 07:50.735
Oh, no.

07:50.737 --> 07:58.844
Just rocking
a party hunch. I like it.
Closer to my booze. To youth.

08:07.453 --> 08:09.287
Can I get a straw?

08:09.289 --> 08:11.223
I must say, there is
something admirable

08:11.225 --> 08:13.258
about the way
Barney wants to
stay young at heart.

08:13.260 --> 08:15.327
I mean,
who wants
to get old?

08:15.329 --> 08:17.028
This guy.

08:17.030 --> 08:21.967
Robin, life is a meal
and old age is the dessert.

08:21.969 --> 08:23.535
I spend so much of my time
worrying about the future.

08:23.537 --> 08:26.271
You know, "Where's my career
going? Who am I gonna marry?"

08:26.273 --> 08:28.406
But
when you're old,
you don't worry,

08:28.408 --> 08:31.042
'cause all that
stuff's already
happened.

08:31.044 --> 08:32.043
Plus, you get to
wear comfy shoes,

08:32.045 --> 08:34.379
and a chair takes you up and
down the stairs. It's perfect.

08:34.381 --> 08:36.681
That's
not perfect.
That's pathetic.

08:36.683 --> 08:40.752
You can't
just jump to the end.
The journey is the best part.

08:40.754 --> 08:43.054
Oh, Robin,
I used to feel
that way, too,

08:43.056 --> 08:47.359
but you'll understand when
you're a little bit older.

08:47.361 --> 08:50.629
Marshall, can you try
not to pick on the
kids today?

08:50.631 --> 08:52.130
I'm not picking
on the kids, Lily.

08:52.132 --> 08:54.833
I'm picking
on the culture of
losing around here.

08:54.835 --> 08:58.103
I got to get them in shape
if they're gonna win that
game tomorrow.

08:58.105 --> 09:02.607
(SCOFFING) Win?
We don't keep score.

09:03.042 --> 09:05.944
What?
We don't keep score.

09:05.946 --> 09:08.146
You don't keep...

09:08.148 --> 09:10.081
What's the point of
playing if you don't

09:10.083 --> 09:11.816
keep score?
How do you know...

09:11.818 --> 09:15.320
Lily,
what were you doing with
this team before I got here?

09:15.322 --> 09:16.788
I was coaching them.

09:16.790 --> 09:17.923
BOY: Whee!

09:17.925 --> 09:19.824
That's it,
my little angels.

09:19.826 --> 09:23.094
You're all luminous,
wonderful beings
of light.

09:23.096 --> 09:24.362
What's the score?

09:24.364 --> 09:27.032
It's all tied
up at fun to fun!

09:27.034 --> 09:29.000
(CHEERING)

09:29.002 --> 09:31.102
Because
that's the point of
playing, to have fun.

09:31.104 --> 09:34.205
No.
The point of playing
is to win the trophy.

09:34.207 --> 09:37.876
And if you don't
know who's winning,
who gets the trophy?

09:37.878 --> 09:41.346
Everyone.
It's a participation trophy.

09:41.348 --> 09:43.281
Everyone gets one.

09:43.283 --> 09:47.752
It's like you're
speaking Chinese
to me right now.

09:47.754 --> 09:48.286
(BEEPS)

09:48.288 --> 09:49.854
Hi, this is Barney.
And Robin.

09:49.856 --> 09:51.323
We can't answer
the phone right
now because...

09:51.325 --> 09:52.824
He's watching
sports and I'm...

09:52.826 --> 09:53.792
Probably out shopping.

09:53.794 --> 09:54.993
(BOTH LAUGHING)

09:54.995 --> 09:55.594
Uh-oh!

09:55.596 --> 09:57.762
Leave a message
and we'll call you
back just as soon...

09:57.764 --> 09:59.030
As...
We...

09:59.032 --> 10:00.999
Can!
Can!

10:01.001 --> 10:02.968
"Leave an annoying
two-person message

10:02.970 --> 10:05.303
"on your answering machine."
Check.

10:05.305 --> 10:09.007
Probably gonna cost me
some dates, but it's okay.

10:09.009 --> 10:11.242
Barney,
your ear's
starting to smell.

10:11.244 --> 10:12.944
No, it's good.

10:12.946 --> 10:18.283
I hate to send it
back, but you did describe
the turkey as extremely lean,

10:18.285 --> 10:21.519
and, well, you tell me.

10:21.921 --> 10:23.622
All right. That's it.

10:23.624 --> 10:24.990
We have our own list.
What?

10:24.992 --> 10:27.792
This is
a list of things
you're too young to do.

10:27.794 --> 10:29.094
Go out and do each
one of these things

10:29.096 --> 10:32.397
and then
tell me you still
want to be an old man.

10:32.399 --> 10:33.031
Hmm.

10:33.033 --> 10:35.400
Remove "Colonoscopy"
and "Have sex with
an old lady,"

10:35.402 --> 10:37.969
and this is a cakewalk.

10:38.337 --> 10:42.807
New stakes, then.
If I can finish your
list before you finish mine,

10:42.809 --> 10:44.709
you have to come
with me to TP
laser tag,

10:44.711 --> 10:46.811
and you have to
buy the toilet paper.

10:46.813 --> 10:50.348
And none of
that biodegradable crap.
I want it up there forever.

10:50.350 --> 10:52.317
Fine, but if I
finish your list first,

10:52.319 --> 10:56.187
it's a six-hour survey
of early 20th-century
American architecture,

10:56.189 --> 10:59.324
and you can never do anything
on the Murtaugh list ever
again.

10:59.326 --> 11:00.759
It's for your own good.

11:00.761 --> 11:03.161
You, sir,
have got yourself a deal.

11:03.163 --> 11:04.863
A gentlemen's agreement!

11:04.865 --> 11:05.730
Huzzah!
Huzzah!

11:05.732 --> 11:07.899
(EXCLAIMING IN PAIN)

11:08.934 --> 11:10.368
Marshall,
they're in
kindergarten.

11:10.370 --> 11:12.771
This isn't how
you teach basketball.

11:12.773 --> 11:14.239
Sure it is.
It's the way I learned.

11:14.241 --> 11:20.145
Are you kidding me? What kind
of sociopath taught you this
way?

11:22.481 --> 11:24.382
Come on, Dad. I'm tired.

11:24.384 --> 11:25.583
Sleep is for winners.

11:25.585 --> 11:28.053
You can go to bed
when you score
a basket.

11:28.055 --> 11:29.087
I'm trying.

11:29.089 --> 11:30.755
Let's give you two
points for trying.

11:30.757 --> 11:35.326
But negative two points
for having a great big
head.

11:35.328 --> 11:41.900
My father
gave me no quarter,
and I asked for no quarter.

11:42.902 --> 11:45.837
I totally gotta call that guy.

11:45.839 --> 11:48.273
Keep stretching!

11:51.544 --> 11:54.245
"Put on reading glasses."
Check.

11:54.247 --> 11:59.284
"Yell at neighborhood kids."
My pleasure.

12:00.352 --> 12:02.153
Hey.
Hey.

12:02.155 --> 12:03.521
What the hell
happened to you?

12:03.523 --> 12:08.193
Oh, I just had a very
minor blew-out-my-knee-and-
it-hurts-like-hell incident.

12:08.195 --> 12:08.893
How'd you blow
out your knee?

12:08.895 --> 12:11.963
We "Helped
someone move out of
a sixth-floor walk-up

12:11.965 --> 12:13.598
"in exchange for pizza
and beer."

12:13.600 --> 12:16.101
Or we helped someone
rob a sixth-floor
walk-up.

12:16.103 --> 12:20.138
They were in
a big hurry and left
all the pictures behind.

12:20.140 --> 12:22.040
Whatevs. It counts.

12:22.042 --> 12:25.810
Now I am off to
"Dye my hair a funny color,"

12:25.812 --> 12:28.713
and then we are
going to "Go to
a rave."

12:28.715 --> 12:30.448
(IMITATING TECHNO MUSIC)
Mmm-hmm.

12:30.450 --> 12:32.450
Ooh! 4:00!
Supper time.

12:32.452 --> 12:34.986
Okay. So,
your dad was
tough on you.

12:34.988 --> 12:38.289
That stinks,
but you don't
have to be like him.

12:38.291 --> 12:39.991
You can learn
from his mistakes.

12:39.993 --> 12:44.295
Mistakes?
Lily, scoreboard.
The guy nailed it, okay?

12:44.297 --> 12:45.130
He taught me
how to be a winner.

12:45.132 --> 12:48.099
That's what I'm
teaching these kids.
And, for that matter,

12:48.101 --> 12:50.101
that's what
I'm gonna teach
our kids someday.

12:50.103 --> 12:54.439
Okay, that's it.
This is not how we're
gonna raise our kids!

12:54.441 --> 12:57.776
And this is
not how you're
gonna coach this team!

12:57.778 --> 13:00.145
At tomorrow's game,
if you are anything less

13:00.147 --> 13:03.848
than a teddy bear
stuffed with cotton
candy and rainbows,

13:03.850 --> 13:07.385
I will silent-treatment
your ass into the ground!

13:07.387 --> 13:09.387
You'll think the time
I found your Internet

13:09.389 --> 13:12.657
search history was
a freaking picnic!

13:12.659 --> 13:14.425
Are we clear?

13:15.394 --> 13:16.861
Lily,
there are
many different...

13:16.863 --> 13:18.363
Are we clear?

13:18.365 --> 13:19.798
Yes, ma'am.

13:23.035 --> 13:24.969
You know,
what's ironic
is that now...

13:24.971 --> 13:26.805
Lily, no!

13:30.976 --> 13:32.744
<i>(TECHNO MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

13:32.746 --> 13:35.513
Just call Ted.
I want to go home.

13:35.515 --> 13:38.950
All right. I'm calling him.
But it's 4:30 in the morning.

13:38.952 --> 13:40.752
He's not
going to be awake.

13:40.754 --> 13:42.921
"Up at 4:00." Check.

13:43.923 --> 13:46.024
Is he answering?
I haven't dialed yet.

13:46.026 --> 13:48.793
Oh, please hurry, Robin.

13:49.328 --> 13:50.628
(PHONE RINGING)

13:50.630 --> 13:54.465
Ooh, perfect.
"Take forever to
answer the phone."

13:57.102 --> 14:02.373
Come on, Ted. Someone gave me
some aspirin and I don't
think it was aspirin.

14:02.375 --> 14:03.808
(EXCLAIMING IN PAIN)

14:03.810 --> 14:05.343
(PHONE RINGING)

14:07.413 --> 14:08.980
(BEEPS)

14:08.982 --> 14:10.448
Check.

14:10.450 --> 14:15.787
So, I know that I have been
a little tough on you for
the past couple days.

14:15.789 --> 14:19.591
And I apologize for that.

14:19.593 --> 14:23.061
So today,
we're not gonna
worry about winning.

14:23.063 --> 14:26.931
We're gonna go out
there and have fun.

14:26.933 --> 14:28.032
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

14:28.034 --> 14:29.167
<i>OLDER TED:</i>
<i>Kids, over the years,</i>

14:29.169 --> 14:30.735
<i>your uncle Marshall</i>
<i>has told and retold</i>

14:30.737 --> 14:32.337
<i>the story of this</i>
<i>game hundreds of</i>
<i>times.</i>

14:32.339 --> 14:36.207
<i>And in reality, the</i>
<i>kids on that other team were</i>
<i>probably only a grade older.</i>

14:36.209 --> 14:41.579
<i>But in telling</i>
<i>and retelling the story,</i>
<i>they came to look like this.</i>

14:47.486 --> 14:49.320
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

14:51.724 --> 14:55.159
Yay!
Way to let them
score that easily.

14:55.161 --> 14:58.396
Now you're sitting down.
Awesome.

15:02.735 --> 15:06.771
Addison, it's not soccer.
You don't kick the ball!

15:07.506 --> 15:09.908
Unless
that's something
that you think is fun,

15:09.910 --> 15:13.645
in which case,
great job having fun.

15:16.649 --> 15:18.883
Whoa,
that was a foul,
wasn't it, ref?

15:18.885 --> 15:20.518
My name's not Ref. It's Kenny.

15:20.520 --> 15:21.853
And watch your tone.

15:21.855 --> 15:24.055
No tone, Kenny.
Great job, Kenny.

15:24.057 --> 15:27.558
Thanks a lot, Kenny.
See you later, Kenny.

15:27.560 --> 15:31.229
All right,
Barney. As your manager,
I'm throwing in the towel.

15:31.231 --> 15:31.996
This bet is over.

15:31.998 --> 15:36.668
Your ear
looks like a free Danish
at a continental breakfast.

15:36.670 --> 15:37.535
(GROANING)

15:37.537 --> 15:39.771
No. No.
One thing left.

15:39.773 --> 15:41.039
"Beer bong."

15:41.041 --> 15:43.908
Oh! Coming right up.

15:45.144 --> 15:49.580
I found
these weird Russian
beers in the basement.

15:49.582 --> 15:51.683
Russian beers?
I'll take a brewski.

15:51.685 --> 15:55.586
(CHUCKLING) Hey.
Brewski. Get it?

15:56.121 --> 15:58.690
Yeah, it's a little warm.

15:58.692 --> 16:00.591
Hope that's
not a problem.

16:00.593 --> 16:02.860
(EXCLAIMING)

16:02.862 --> 16:05.630
Don't. Okay.
Don't, don't, don't.

16:05.632 --> 16:06.998
(EXCLAIMING)

16:07.000 --> 16:09.834
All right, Ted.
You win. I hate this.

16:09.836 --> 16:13.338
I hate all of it.
My back is killing me.

16:13.340 --> 16:15.940
Everyone at the rave
thought I was a narc.

16:15.942 --> 16:19.310
My ear hurts so
bad I can hear it.

16:19.312 --> 16:23.848
I can
hear my own ear.
Think about that.

16:23.850 --> 16:24.349
My clothes...

16:24.351 --> 16:26.117
What is it...
What is it...
What am I...

16:26.119 --> 16:27.685
Get this stuff off of me!

16:27.687 --> 16:30.688
Ted, I'll pay you
double for your
finest suit.

16:30.690 --> 16:33.558
Here's 30 bucks.

16:33.892 --> 16:35.927
And throw in the shoes.

16:36.495 --> 16:37.161
You win, Ted.

16:37.163 --> 16:43.001
I'll never do anything
on the Murtaugh list again.
I'm too old for this stuff.

16:43.003 --> 16:46.504
You know,
Barney, last night,
I went to bed at 8:00

16:46.506 --> 16:48.039
because it was on the list,

16:48.041 --> 16:51.175
and I couldn't sleep
because, well, it
was 8:00.

16:51.177 --> 16:54.345
So I decided to
watch<i> Lethal Weapon.</i>

16:56.015 --> 17:00.785
<i>And then, when</i>
I still couldn't sleep,
I watched ethal Weapon 2.

17:00.787 --> 17:03.721
<i>And then I watched</i> .

17:03.723 --> 17:06.224
<i>And then,</i>
<i>halfway through</i>
<i>Lethal Weapon 4</i>

17:06.226 --> 17:07.792
<i>is when it occurred to me.</i>

17:07.794 --> 17:10.862
Murtaugh kept saying,
"I'm too old for
this stuff,"

17:10.864 --> 17:15.800
but every time he'd say it,
he'd turn around, make
another movie

17:15.802 --> 17:18.002
and do more stuff.

17:18.004 --> 17:20.738
I guess what
I'm saying is,

17:22.107 --> 17:23.708
screw being old.

17:24.643 --> 17:26.711
Let's go TP laser tag, huh?

17:26.713 --> 17:27.979
Yeah.

17:27.981 --> 17:30.581
And then the hospital.

17:33.252 --> 17:34.252
Great job, guys.

17:34.254 --> 17:37.355
At least we're not
keeping score, right?
No idea what the score is.

17:37.357 --> 17:40.858
Could be 53 to zero.
Could be some other score.

17:40.860 --> 17:42.560
It's 53 to zero.

17:42.562 --> 17:45.630
What are we
doing wrong,
Coach?

17:45.632 --> 17:47.532
You know what?
You're not doing
anything wrong.

17:47.534 --> 17:49.367
It's great that
you guys are losing,

17:49.369 --> 17:53.438
because in life,
it doesn't matter how
much effort you put in,

17:53.440 --> 17:57.442
or how hard you try,
people will just
give you things

17:57.444 --> 18:00.545
like diplomas and
jobs and promotions.

18:00.547 --> 18:05.450
So, it doesn't matter
what you do out there,
as long as you have fun.

18:05.452 --> 18:08.619
<i>OLDER TED: At that point,</i>
<i>because they didn't want to</i>
<i>fight in front of the kids,</i>

18:08.621 --> 18:09.987
<i>your uncle Marshall</i>
<i>and aunt Lily</i>

18:09.989 --> 18:12.623
<i>had one of their</i>
<i>telepathic conversations.</i>

18:12.625 --> 18:13.925
<i>LILY: Don't you</i>
<i>give me that look.</i>

18:13.927 --> 18:15.927
<i>MARSHALL:</i>
<i>Lily, I can't</i>
<i>take it anymore!</i>

18:15.929 --> 18:17.762
<i>Your way of</i>
<i>coaching is crazy!</i>

18:17.764 --> 18:19.864
<i>LILY: Stop yelling at me!</i>

18:19.866 --> 18:21.132
<i>MARSHALL: Sorry.</i>

18:21.134 --> 18:23.768
<i>But can I please do it</i>
<i>my way?</i>

18:23.770 --> 18:30.108
<i>LILY: Fine, but I'm going</i>
<i>to do it my way, too. I'm</i>
<i>getting my guitar.</i>

18:30.909 --> 18:33.678
<i>OLDER TED:</i>
<i>I don't know if it was</i>
<i>Marshall's tough attitude,</i>

18:33.680 --> 18:34.745
<i>Lily's gentle encouragement</i>

18:34.747 --> 18:37.115
<i>or some magical</i>
<i>combination of</i>
<i>the two,</i>

18:37.117 --> 18:38.816
<i>but in the second</i>
<i>half of that game,</i>

18:38.818 --> 18:41.752
<i>that ragtag group of</i>
<i>little firecrackers</i>

18:42.688 --> 18:45.823
<i>got beat down even worse.</i>

18:47.059 --> 18:49.460
<i>In fact, according to</i>
<i>your uncle Marshall,</i>

18:49.462 --> 18:52.163
<i>in the second half, the</i>
<i>other team got even taller.</i>

18:52.165 --> 18:54.866
<i>And one of them</i>
<i>turned into a Teen Wolf.</i>

18:54.868 --> 18:58.002
Kenny!
There is a Teen
Wolf on the court!

18:58.004 --> 18:59.837
That can't be legal.

18:59.839 --> 19:01.973
I know the Teen Wolf
looks different, kids,

19:01.975 --> 19:05.610
but try to make
sure he feels
included.

19:08.680 --> 19:10.615
(HOWLING)

19:13.819 --> 19:15.653
Oh, yeah!

19:20.325 --> 19:22.326
(HOWLING)

19:25.030 --> 19:26.864
How is that not
traveling, Kenny?

19:26.866 --> 19:29.700
You're killing me!
You are absolutely
killing me!

19:29.702 --> 19:32.069
Hey, watch it, Coach,
or you'll get a technical.

19:32.071 --> 19:36.741
Oh, Kenny,
I'm begging you to
give me a technical.

19:36.743 --> 19:37.875
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

19:37.877 --> 19:39.243
<i>OLDER TED:</i>
<i>When the final</i>
<i>horn mercifully blew,</i>

19:39.245 --> 19:43.614
<i>the score</i>
<i>was, by Marshall's</i>
<i>estimate, 118 to nothing.</i>

19:43.616 --> 19:45.750
<i>And even though they</i>
<i>didn't win anything,</i>

19:45.752 --> 19:49.654
<i>everyone, even the coach,</i>
<i>got a participation trophy.</i>

19:49.656 --> 19:52.557
I understand if
you don't want it.

19:53.759 --> 19:55.626
I love it.

19:56.562 --> 19:58.462
I just... I worked
so hard. It feels good

19:58.464 --> 20:00.498
to be
appreciated
for my effort.

20:00.500 --> 20:02.633
I know, baby.

20:05.604 --> 20:09.507
Maybe your way is
not totally stupid.

20:09.509 --> 20:10.708
Thanks.

20:10.710 --> 20:13.644
Your way is
totally stupid.

20:19.651 --> 20:20.818
Ow!

20:20.820 --> 20:22.753
McCRACKEN: Stinson!

20:25.524 --> 20:26.490
Son,

20:26.492 --> 20:31.662
you have been a pain in
my ass ever since you
joined this club.

20:31.664 --> 20:38.536
But damn it, if this ain't
some of the finest TP
work I've ever seen.

20:38.538 --> 20:42.773
You're reinstated,
effective immediately.

20:42.775 --> 20:44.041
Really?

20:46.411 --> 20:50.114
Hell, no!
I'm calling the police!

20:50.116 --> 20:52.950
Grown-ass
man with pink hair
throwing toilet paper.

20:52.952 --> 20:55.052
You've got
to be kidding me,
I'm too old for this...

20:55.054 --> 20:59.090
<i>OLDER TED: Stuff,</i>
<i>he said, "Stuff."</i>
